This repository contains the Report (Listener) microservice, implemented using Spring Boot and Maven.
The service is containerized using Docker and configured to start with external integrations disabled.

Disabled integrations include:
ActiveMQ (JMS)
Database (JDBC / JPA)
Eureka Client

Technology Stack
Java 17
Spring Boot
Maven
Docker

Disabled Integrations Configuration
File: src/main/resources/application-disabled.yml
"""
spring:
  autoconfigure:
    exclude:
      - org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.jms.activemq.ActiveMQAutoConfiguration
      - org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.jms.JmsAutoConfiguration
      - org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.jdbc.DataSourceAutoConfiguration
      - org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.orm.jpa.HibernateJpaAutoConfiguration

eureka:
  client:
    enabled: false

spring:
  profiles:
    default: disabled
"""

This configuration ensures the service starts without connecting to any external systems.

Dockerfile:
"""
# ---- Build stage ----
FROM maven:3.9-eclipse-temurin-17 AS build
WORKDIR /app

COPY pom.xml .
COPY .mvn/ .mvn/
COPY mvnw .
RUN mvn -q -DskipTests dependency:go-offline || true

COPY src ./src
RUN mvn -DskipTests package

# ---- Run stage ----
FROM eclipse-temurin:17-jre
WORKDIR /app

COPY --from=build /app/target/*.jar app.jar
EXPOSE 8080

ENTRYPOINT ["java","-jar","/app/app.jar"]
"""

Building the Docker Image

Run the following command from the project root directory:
"""
docker build -t trainer-workload-service:disabled .
"""

Running the Application
The application listens on port 8080.
"""
docker run -p 8080:8080 trainer-workload-service:disabled
"""
Access
http://localhost:8080
